\begin{align*}
(x-2)+(x-1)+x+(x+1)+(x+2)&=5\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 5x&=5\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=1
\end{align*}
So, the five integers are $-1$, $0$, $1$, $2$, and $3$. The product of these integers is
\begin{align*}
(-1)(0)(1)(2)(3)&=\boxed{-6}
\end{align*}
