&= \frac{12x^3}{x^2} \cdot \frac{5}{14x} \\
&= \frac{60x}{14} \\
&= \boxed{5x}
\end{align*}

Note that we can cancel out the $x$ terms in the numerator and denominator because we are assuming $x \ne 0$.

